{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsQH2kCcWEfXmxxMNB5J","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. The root cause was a RabbitMQ permission gap: `app-user` had `write`/`read` but empty `configure` permission on the `/app` vhost, so it couldn't declare `app-queue` via the management API. I granted `configure` (and reaffirmed write/read) with `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"`, then recycled the producer pod.\n\nCurrent state:\n- `app-producer` is `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts, no more crash loop.\n- `/app` vhost has `app-queue` of type `classic` with messages actively accumulating (10 and growing).\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are up and in cluster status as disk+running nodes — no data loss, no CRDs/operators touched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":943,"cache_read_input_tokens":34812,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":943},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ca0a2d40-cbf1-4bb1-b851-96717345c42b","uuid":"74d8dbc2-9c27-4dca-ae63-ba95e631adcd","request_id":"req_011CcsQH1jvTXZMmZvjcGJsr"}
